.nh
.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-footprints - Summarize logged per-service resource footprints


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel footprints [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Summarize the per-service resource footprint history recorded by the
background sampler (\fBcitadel work\fR writes one sample per minute).

.PP
For each managed service it reports average/peak RAM, average/peak VRAM,
average/peak CPU, the fraction of samples that were idle, the longest idle
stretch, and the sample count + time window.

.PP
The raw rows live in rotated daily CSVs under ~/citadel-node/footprints/
(footprints-YYYY-MM-DD.csv) and are directly DuckDB/pandas-queryable for
ad-hoc analysis, e.g.:

.PP
duckdb -c "SELECT service, avg(rss_mb), max(rss_mb) \\
    FROM '~/citadel-node/footprints/*.csv' GROUP BY 1 ORDER BY 2 DESC"

.PP
The node-level row is recorded under the service name "_node" and carries
host CPU/RAM plus total GPU utilisation and VRAM used.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for footprints

.PP
\fB--idle-only\fP[=false]
	Only include samples where the node was idle

.PP
\fB--service\fP=""
	Restrict to a single service name

.PP
\fB--since\fP=""
	Only include samples newer than this duration (e.g. 30m, 1h, 6h)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Summarize all services over the last hour
  citadel footprints --since 1h

  # One service only
  citadel footprints --service vllm --since 6h

  # Only samples where the node was idle
  citadel footprints --idle-only --since 24h
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
